@node "NEWAREA" "Adding File Areas"
 step 1) Load SX-Config, and click "Conf/File/Msg" button.
        Click on "MAIN" and then change the "No. of File Areas" to what
        ever number you need.

     2) Click "Menus/Commands" in SX-Config and choose "FileAreas"
        Click "ADD" and add a new command, eg "3" then "4" etc
        Set these fields for your new command (or simular)

        Command                : 3                        Extra Number: 3
        Low Access        : 0                        High Access : 255
        Function ID        : 53
        Door/String/File: FileList_Menu

        This will make the BBS set the file area to "3" (extra number) and
        jump to the FileList_Menu, if the user hits the "3" key.

     3) Edit the tooltypes of SX:Confs/Main.info (click the icon once
        and choose "Information" from workbench".
        Change the NDIRS tool type to the same value you chose for
        "No. Of File Areas" in step 1.

     4) Edit SX:Screens/FileAreas.ANS and add your new area!
@endnode

