@node "conv" "The UserBase Converters"

 @{b}@{bg shine}UserBase Converters@{ub}@{bg back}

 If you like to change the BBS to SX (eSSeXX) you may convert your
 UserBase to a SX valid userbase file.
 Actually you can convert DayDream and MAXS userbases to SX.

 @{b}DD_to_SX@{ub}        - attempts to open "@{b}daydream:data/userbase.dat@{ub}" and
                   writes a coverted SX userbase in ram:. If you want
                   to use the new userbase, move it to SX:

 @{b}MAXS_to_SX@{ub}      - must be run with arguments:

                   @{b}MAXS_to_SX <maxsbase>@{ub}

                   eg:
                        @{b}MAXS_to_SX BBS:UserFiles/User.DATA@{ub}

                   This will also write the SX userbase into RAM:

 @{"!ĀIMPORTANTĀ!" link "" 0}

        If you are going to use a converted userbase, you must
        make sure every access level your users may have is in
        @{"SX-Config->Access" link "con_axxset" 0} prefs. Make sure all the ratios/conf-
        access is how you want it to be. Most importantly, turn
        *ON* the "@{b}@{bg shine}Force this set on users@{ub}@{bg back}" for every entry! This
        will make sure that all users get the correct and new
        ratios/confaccess when they next login.


 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}
@endnode

@node "dddp" "DayDream Door Support"

 @{b}@{bg shine}Doors - DayDream DDDP@{ub}@{bg back}

 System-X also runs alot of Daydream doors. 
 This section is still under development and will get better. 
 If you find a Daydream door that will not work with SX properly,
 contact me and I'll add any necessary door commands to make it work.

 Some DayDream doors need the directoy @{b}DD:data/@{ub} or DD:configs/ . 
 These directories are already created on SX: and some needed Files
 are in tere, too.
 If any error comes up, while using DDDP doors (or any other type)
 you can use SnoopDos for more information, on what the task does 
 not find...maybe you only have to create a special directory or so..

 DayDream doors that won't work:

        - Message Base related doors
        - File Base related doors (file listers)
 
 For the usage of DDDP doors you need the @{b}DreamDoor.Library@{ub} from the
 DayDream main archives.
 The lib should be in the archive.
 
 
 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}  @{"Doors" link "doors" 0}
@endnode

