@node "faq" "Frequently asked questions"

 @{b}@{bg shine}Frequently Asked Questions@{ub}@{bg back}

 @{bg fill}Why doesn't the last callers ansi update ?@{bg back}
 Firstly, you must have @{"BBS:ĀassignedĀtoĀSX:" link "startbat" 0}
 To begin using the last callers programm @{b}SAmiLog@{ub}, you must execute this
 in shell: "@{b}SX:Utils/SAmiLog -C@{ub}" (this will create a storage file)
 Also make sure your @{b}sx:batch/logoff.bat@{ub} file has the +s flag.
 i.e.:

  @{b}logoff.bat                   342 -s--rw-d 26-Jul-97 13:09:55@{ub}
                                    ^
                                    |
                                    ` @{b}Script flag@{ub}
 If it doesn't, type this:
                                    @{b}Protect SX:Batch/LogOff.BAT +s@{ub}

 @{bg fill}Why doesn't ToySent or other DayDream doors work ?@{bg back}
 Type this in shell:
                       "@{b}setenv dreamutils SX:Configs/@{ub}" 

 or add this line to your user-startup or your SX-startbatch.

 @{bg fill}Why do I get a requestor to insert "FIFO:" ?@{bg back}
 Install fifo.library & handler! Grab it from AmiNet.

 @{bg fill}Why do shell doors or AED lockup/crash ?@{bg back}
 You must give fifo a stack of 8192, in your startup-sequence:

 @{b}stack 8192
 run NIL: l:fifo-handler
 stack 4096@{ub}
        
 (read the docs to FIFO.library for more information)

 @{bg fill}Why do i need FILES:FCheckX/ ?@{bg back}
 This Dir must not have the name FCheck/ . I call it i.e. PlayPen/
 like the /X one, ..any /X door wants that, but does not run...
 If there is an Upload, the file will be placed in the FileCheckDir.
 You set the Path in SX-Config->ThisNode->FileCheckDir. 
 If the File is checked by the FileCheckDoors, it will be copied to
 dest. conference.
 If the directory does not exists, the file are copied to >nil: .
 This needs to be changed ..

 @{bg fill}How can i easy create a List with the Downloadpaths ?@{bg back}
 Try the `list`-command like :

 @{b}list <yourdevice> lformat="%f%s/" ALL DIRS >ram:Paths@{ub}

 Dont forgot to add the Path of the Conference to the top of the List, 
 from what you like to put the Pathlist in.
 This is usefull, if you use Doors like CD-Server from Siegel/ByteAndy 
 of TRSI.

 @{bg fill}How can i use my Homelanguage under SystemX ?@{bg back}
 Lets create it for i.e. Swedish language...
 First refer to @{"SX-Config->DisplayModes" link "convdismods" 0} and add a new DisplayMode
 called @{b}ANSI_SWD@{ub}
 Create a Directory, were you like to store you localised
 ANSI's, i.e. @{b}SX:Screens/SWD@{ub}
 Give a specific Extension to all your ANSI's and enter that in the
 Extensionfield @{bg shine}SWD@{bg back} so all ansis are named i.e. @{b}#?.swd@{ub} are selected,
 if you @{"login" link "sx_login" 0} under your new ANSI_SWD Mode.
 You have to edit the @{"SX:TXT/Strings.xxx" link "strings" 0}, too, and copy it to your
 @{b}Strings.swd@{ub} . It is no problem, to put the #?.swd files between the
 #?.ans or #?.txt files.
 Dont forget, to create a new menu and a new commands.xxx.swd file.
 


 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}
@endnode

@node "fcheck" "Using a filecheck door"

 @{b}@{bg shine}FileCheck doors@{ub}@{bg back}

 A FileCheck door is a tool, to do something with the file, after the
 user has uploaded.
 The FileCheck door can be a dizzer, adder, stripper, checker, ... 

 To use a filecheck door, you must create a textfile:

    @{b}SX:Confs/<path>/FileCheck.DAT@{ub}

 where @{b}<path>@{ub} is the path of the conference you want to effect.

 This will be a text file which may look like this:

 @{b}1
 Doors:FileCheck 
 6 
 Doors:LameChecker@{ub}

 The above example would run a XIM door called `FileCheck` 
 and after that, a STDIO door called `LameChecker`.

 The types are:

       @{bg fill} 1 @{bg back} - @{"XIMĀAmiExpressĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "xim" 0} 
       @{bg fill} 2 @{bg back} - @{"AIMĀAmiExpressĀAREXX" link "aim" 0}   
       @{bg fill} 3 @{bg back} - @{"ParagonĀ/ĀMAXsBBSĀĀĀ" link "para" 0}    
       @{bg fill} 4 @{bg back} - @{"DayDreamĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "dddp" 0}   
       @{bg fill} 5 @{bg back} - @{"DayDreamĀAREXXĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "ddrx" 0}    
       @{bg fill} 6 @{bg back} - @{"STDIO/Dos/ShellĀĀĀĀĀ" link "shell" 0}         
       @{bg fill} 7 @{bg back} - @{"FAMEĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "fame" 0}  
 
 @{bg highlight}! Important !@{bg back}     

        You must not put any special characters or extra carriage returns
        in this file, each door must take up 2 lines only. Also don't put
        any extra carriage returns at the end of the file!

@{b} Arguments@{ub} 

        The door will be sent 2 arguments (paramaters), the first is the
        node number, as usual, and the 2nd is the filename of the file
        to check.

@{b} Note@{ub}

        If your door moves or deletes the file, System-X
        will not add the file to the filelist.

 An example FileCheck door is included in @{b}SX:Developer/SASC/@{ub} as source.

 
 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}
@endnode

@node "fea" "Features"

 @{b}@{bg shine}Features@{ub}@{bg back}

 The archive includes all needed files to run a full configurable
 Bulletin Board System. There are serveral utilities posted with
 this archive (@{"sx:utils/" link "utils" 0})

 SX (eSSeXX) has a lot of features:

        - Supports 7 door types:
                        - @{"AmiExpressĀ(XIM)ĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "xim" 0}   
                        - @{"AmiExpressĀAREXXĀ(AIM)" link "aim" 0}    
                        - @{"DayDreamĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "dddp" 0}  
                        - @{"DayDreamĀAREXXĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "ddrx" 0}        
                        - @{"Paragon/MAXsBBSĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "para" 0}    
                        - @{"Shell/Dos/STDIOĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "shell" 0}        
                        - @{"FAMEĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "fame" 0}    
        - full flexable Bulletin Board System
        - up to 256 Conferences
        - up to 256 Fileares per Conference
        - up to 500 MsgBases per Conference
        - Partially compatable with /X
        - XPR protocol support (xpr#?modem.library)
        - HydraCom/SModem support.
        - comfortable @{"GUIĀConfig" link "sxconfig" 0} 
        - comfortable @{"GUIĀUserEd" link "guiusered" 0}
        - lots of @{"internalĀFunctions" link "func" 0} 
        - supports @{"MCI-Commands" link "mci" 0}
        - ARexxĀport @{"SX-MCP" link "mcprexx" 0}        
        - Line and Fullscreen @{"MessageĀEditor" link "sx_msged" 0} with fileattachment
        - easy CommandMenu creation
        - full MCI-Code support on all ansis shown by SX
                  - CommandLine interface for buffered commands
                  - stable Support
        - nearly all is editable by the sysop
        - ...

 The List is long ...


 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}
@endnode

@node "fifo" "FIFO handler"

 @{b}@{bg shine}The Fifo-Handler@{ub}@{bg back}
 
 Copy the fifo-handler and its icon to your L: directory.
 (This is already done by the installer)

 Copy the fifo.library to your Libs: directory.
 (This is already done by the installer)

 For the usage you have to add the following lines to your
 user-startup (This is NOT done by the installer):

 @{b};BEGIN FIFO
 run >NIL: <NIL: L:Fifo-Handler
 ;END FIFO@{ub}
 
 The icon of the fifo-handler contains the needed stack of 8192,
 but you can set the stack manually bevor you run the fifo-handler.

 @{b};BEGIN FIFO
 stack 8192
 run >NIL: <NIL: L:Fifo-Handler
 ;END FIFO@{ub}

 thats it...


 @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}  @{"Doors" link "doors" 0}
@endnode

