@node "sx-mcp" "The MCP window"

 @{b}@{bg shine}Master Control Program@{ub}@{bg back}

 This represents the Mainwindow of SX (eSSeXX). 
 Serveral buttons give you good control about the node and gave ya
 out some informations. An @{"ARexx-port" link "mcprexx" 0} is available, too and some
 @{"utils" link "utils" 13} let control you the node by script or CLI.
 
 @{bg shine}SX_MCP window:@{bg back}

 @{b} Iconify@{ub} - `@{bg highlight}I@{bg back}`-gadget in the right upper edge of the window.
            Gets the window Iconified with App-Icon on WB.

@{b} NodeList@{ub} - Select the node by mouseclick in the nodelist.
            If no node is launched, doubleclick will lauch the
            node like set in @{"SX-Config->ThisNode" link "con_thisnode" 0}.
            If the node is lauched, the screen comes up.
            How many nodes you like to see in the nodelist
            you set in the MCP Prefs window. Set Realnames there
            too, if you like.
            Over that the node shows under `@{b}ACTION/DOOR@{ub}` the 
            activities, the user did.

 @{bg shine}Control Gadgeds:@{bg back}

  @{b}Open Screen@{ub} - @{"selectĀtheĀnode" link "con_selnode" 0} you like in the list and press here
                to open the current nodescreen.

 @{b}Close Screen@{ub} - select the node in the list and press here to close
                its screen. 

   @{b}Lauch Node@{ub} - select the node from list and Launch with this button.
                You may also do a doubleclick in the list to lauch the 
                node.

    @{b}Shut Down@{ub} - select the node from list and click here to shutdown the 
                node. If the @{"nodescreen" link "nodescreen" 0} is already open, just click F10
                in it, to close.

   @{b}Enter Chat@{ub} - select the node yo like to @{"chat" link "sx_chat" 0} and then click here.

    @{b}Kick User@{ub} - select the node from list and click here to kick the
                user on the selected node. You will be asked by requester
                if you are really really shure ? No logoffbatch or so
                is run here. Just a kick...

   @{b}MCP-Config@{ub} - Go to the @{"MCP-Config" link "sx-mcp" 0} window. 
                Its not needed to shut down SX while you change settings 
                here.

   @{b}Shut Nodes@{ub} - Shut down all nodes. If users are online, you will be
                prompted, nothing happens then.

   @{b}Sysop Away@{ub} - Click here to enter a reason, why you are not chatable.
                The reason is typed out to the user if he pages you
                and you are not available for @{"chat" link "sx_chat" 0}.
                ...surely only if the bevelbox right of the
                button is flagged!

    @{b}SX-Config@{ub} - Got to the @{"SC-Config" link "sxconfig" 0} window. Remember that you have to 
                shut down SX for most changes here.-

  @{b}UserButtons@{ub} - set your own programs in here. You can configure these
                buttons in MCP-Config. 
                i.e. enter a cronjob manager here or a button `NetCall`;)

 @{b}The Scroll Gadget:@{ub}

 @{b}User Information@{ub} - give Informations to the user, logged on the node,
                    you selected in the nodelist.
     @{b}Last Callers@{ub} - ...the lost invaders from space   
     @{b}Last Uploads@{ub} - List of the last uploads
   @{b}Last Downloads@{ub} - List of the last Downloads
   @{b}About System-X@{ub} - nice About. ZED, i like yer games :)
   @{i}UserButtonBank@{ui} - its planned. 15 new gadgeds for yer own usage.
                    Not in this version :(

 
  @{"Main" link "MAIN" 0}
@endnode

